parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause extended stopping distances, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brakes do not respond properly when hitting bumps or uneven road surfaces.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking accelerator pedal can cause rapid acceleration, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal sticks in the up position
requiring tapping to move it to accelerate
sometimes causing rapid acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The persistent squeaking noise from the brakes can be a sign of a underlying problem, potentially leading to brake failure and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Squeaking noise from the brakes
despite repeated repairs and maintenance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system problems can cause a range of issues, including brake and accelerator malfunctions, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Problems with the electrical system
including issues with the brakes and accelerator.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front hub assembly can cause the wheel to separate from the vehicle, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The wheel may fall off
the vehicle may vibrate
the ABS system may malfunction
the sending unit may fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration at high speeds can cause loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates at speeds of 38mph or higher

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tailgate cables can cause the tailgate to fall unexpectedly, potentially injuring people or damaging the vehicle, and may lead to accidents or other safety hazards.
symptoms: The tailgate cables snap or break

the tailgate does not stay in place
